Sentencas: In this study the bilayer composite electrodes based on LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-delta (LNF) electronic conductor and Bi2O3-based electrolytes doped with Er (Bi1.6Er0.4O3, EDB) and Y (Bi1.5Y0.5O3, YDB) have been developed and their performance has been investigated in the dependence on the electrolyte content and sintering conditions.
Titulo: Development of composite LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-based air electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells with a thin-film bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the optimized electrodes with electrolyte content of 50 wt % in the functional layer and with the LNF-EDB-CuO collector is in a range of 0.65-1.09 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C and 0.10-0.12 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Development of composite LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-based air electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells with a thin-film bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: The polarization characteristics of the Bi-based electrodes are compared with those for the composite electrodes based on LNF and Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC).
Titulo: Development of composite LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-based air electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells with a thin-film bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: The developed electrodes have been tested in a SOFC mode in the anode-supported cells with a thin film electrolyte of YSZ/YDC (Y-doped zirconia/ceria).
Titulo: Development of composite LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-based air electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells with a thin-film bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: The single cells with such cathodes are shown to have performance characteristics that are several times higher than that for the cell with a standard platinum cathode.
Titulo: Development of composite LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-based air electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells with a thin-film bilayer electrolyte

Sentencas: This is due to the optimized content and dispersity of the components; high conductivity of ionic and electronic constituents of the composite electrodes; greatly extended triple phase boundary (TPB) of the electrochemical reaction and advanced electrode design with collector providing uniform current distribution.
Titulo: Development of composite LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-based air electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells with a thin-film bilayer electrolyte
